Who can tell? Wed aubum Phyllis; Rich may be your kin:

Could she know her royal stoek, and Kind Penates win!

No, the girl is not descended From the rascal crowd:

Loyal, clear os greed, she surely Owns a mother proud.

Arms, and sace, and tapering ankles Unreproached I gauge.

Who suspects me? Eight my lustres, And my shield, mine age.
